New Records: Jaime Jaquez Jr. recorded his first career triple-double with 16 points, 12 rebounds, and 10 assists.
Key Match Events: DeMar DeRozan scored nine of Sacramento’s 11 points in the second overtime, including several clutch jumpers.
Jaime Jaquez Jr. missed critical free throws in the first overtime.
Tyler Herro committed a costly 8-second violation late in the fourth quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Heat head coach Erik Spoelstra expressed determination to learn from the tough losses and fight for a breakthrough.
